{"word":"κεντέω","slug":"κεντέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κεντέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>epic <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>κένσαι</el> as if from <el>κέντω</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to prick, goad, spur on</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of bees and wasps, <i>to sting</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>generally, <i>to prick, stab</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <i>to torture</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>σὺν δόλωι κ.</el> <i>to stab</i> in the dark, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}